Package net.cabezudo.json.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ElementNotExistException
    Thrown when an application tried to get a non existent element from a JSONArray or JSONObject.
    EmptyQueueException
    Thrown when has been reached the endo of the token queue while parsing a JSON string.
    EOSException
    Thrown when an end of string has been reached unexpectedly while parsing a JSON string.
    JSONConvertionException
    Thrown when the conversion between one object to another is not possible.
    JSONParseException
    Thrown when an error has been reached unexpectedly while parsing a JSON string.
    NotPropertiesException
    Thrown when is when a POJO generate a JSONObject without properties because there isn't any JSONProperty annotations in POJO properties.
    ObjectException
    Thrown when is not possible access to an Java object property.
    PropertyNotExistException
    Thrown when an application tried to get a non existent property from an object.
    UnexpectedElementException
    Thrown when an invalid element if found while parsing a JSON string.
